@startuml
title Checkout Flow Centered On checkout-service
caption Core synchronous path only. Pricing is Go. Kafka side effects happen after the order exists.
hide footbox

actor "API Client\nmobile / web / partner" as Client
participant "checkout-service\nworkflow + temp state" as Checkout
participant "cart-service\nactive cart state" as Cart
participant "pricing-service\nGo / gRPC quote" as Pricing
participant "inventory-service\nreserve stock" as Inventory
participant "payment-service\nauthorize funds" as Payment
participant "order-service\ndurable order" as Order

Client -> Checkout: 1. POST /checkouts/{id}/place-order
Checkout -> Cart: 2. load cart snapshot
Cart --> Checkout: cart lines + selections
Checkout -> Pricing: 3. gRPC quote(cart, address, coupon)
Pricing --> Checkout: priced totals + quote expiry
Checkout -> Inventory: 4. reserve(items)
Inventory --> Checkout: reservationId + reservation expiry
Checkout -> Payment: 5. authorize(amount, payment method)
Payment --> Checkout: authorizationId
Checkout -> Order: 6. create immutable order from snapshot
Order --> Checkout: orderId
Checkout --> Client: 7. 201 Created + orderId

note over Checkout
Why checkout-service exists:
it owns short-lived checkout state,
idempotency, retries, and compensation
across cart, pricing, inventory, payment,
and order creation.
end note

note over Checkout, Order #Fef2f2
Compensation handled by checkout-service:
- pricing mismatch: fail before reservation and payment authorization
- payment failure: release inventory reservation
- order creation failure after auth:
  void payment authorization and release reservation
end note
@enduml
